s need to be able to use the protocol anytime, no matter who=E2=80=99s tryi=
ng to stop it, for a long time.=C2=A0
To do that, it=E2=80=99s separating the security the protocol is responsibl=
e for from the security that the application and underlying blockchain are =
responsible for.=C2=A0
The intrinsic security, the infrastructure, needs to work reliably and pred=
ictably over time, but the extrinsic security needs to be modular and contr=
olled by the application so that it can evolve as technology advances. As b=
etter validators or zero-knowledge clients, like Polyhedra, enter the marke=
t, applications should be able to plug them in.=C2=A0
Applications should also be able to choose how much extrinsic security they=
