nefits as technology and competition push out the Pareto Frontier.=C2=A0
This is one of the most important changes in v2, and the first that Bryan h=
ighlighted when we spoke: instead of Oracles and Relayers, which were good =
in theory but hard in practice, there are Decentralized Verifier Networks a=
nd Executors, which are which are permissionless to run, easier to implemen=
t (open sourced examples exist), and endlessly configurable.
