&#128075;, </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Happy Thursday! </p><p style=3D"color: rgb=
(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Cryp=
to, pronounced dead in 2022, has come back to life. If you&#8217;ve been re=
ading Not Boring through that period, you would have known that it would co=
me back eventually. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But just because token prices are=
 back up doesn&#8217;t mean that crypto is anywhere close to doing the thin=
gs that I think it will be able to do. Better infrastructure will need to t=
ranslate into better applications, which will demand better infrastructure,=
 and on and on. It&#8217;s a never-ending project. </p><p style=3D"color: r=
gb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">La=
yerZero Labs is building foundational infrastructure for crypto all the way=
 at the foundation&#8230; LayerZero. It&#8217;s an omnichain messaging prot=
ocol, a transport layer that allows applications to send messages containin=
g bytes of information from one chain to another. If it succeeds, each bloc=
kchain will be like a node in one larger, more performant network. </p><p s=
tyle=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Today, it&#8217;s rolling out v2 of its protocol. I got=
 an early look, and I&#8217;m excited to explain what it is and why I think=
 it&#8217;s going to be important. Apologies for the late send &#8212; v2 i=
s </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/3e8b77c0-10d3-42bf-8536-4=
c6cac3ae201?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkR=
NpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">hot =
off the presses</a><span>.</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); fo=
nt-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">This essay is a Spon=
sored Deep Dive. While the piece is sponsored, these are all my real and ge=
nuine views. I haven&#8217;t written as many of them this year as I have be=
fore because I&#8217;m only writing them on companies that I think have a c=
hance to be really important in an area I care about, and LayerZero Labs fi=
ts that bill.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I&#8217;ve been a fan of LayerZero since=
 I had LayerZero Labs CEO Bryan Pellegrino on Not Boring Founders in early =
2022, and I&#8217;m impressed with the improvements they&#8217;ve made in v=
2 and the potential of the business model. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 6=
4, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>You =
can read more about how I choose which companies to do deep dives on, and h=
