hem away, and then waiting for a painfully long time. More than once, I&#82=
17;ve worried if my tokens were lost forever while I waited.&#160;</span></=
p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; m=
argin: 0 0 20px 0;">At launch, Bryan did a video comparing LayerZero to bri=
dges that shows how slow bridging can be:&#160;</p><a href=3D"https://subst=
ack.com/redirect/61db479f-b915-49f0-9584-560361dbb511?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3Qif=
Q.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" target=3D"_blank" class=3D"y=
outube-wrap" data-component-name=3D"Youtube2ToDOMStatic" style=3D"display: =
block; margin: 1.6em 0;"><img src=3D"https://substackcdn.com/image/youtube/=
w_550,c_limit/l_youtube_play_qyqt8q,w_120/JFnF1dgbF00" style=3D"-ms-interpo=
lation-mode: bicubic; border: none !important; display: block; height: auto=
; margin: 0 auto; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; width: 100%;"></=
a><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; m=
argin: 0 0 20px 0;">So the trio realized that they&#8217;d need to go deepe=
r into the stack to solve the problem. They&#8217;d need to build foundatio=
nal infrastructure on top of which bridges could be built. They&#8217;d nee=
d to build a protocol that would transport arbitrary messages across blockc=
hains.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">LayerZero was born.&#160;</p><p style=3D"=
color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20p=
x 0;">By building a messaging protocol instead of a bridge, LayerZero Labs =
eliminated the idea of locking and wrapping tokens, got rid of the honeypot=
, bundled a bunch of steps into one message, and removed the need to worry =
about gas.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Chain A sends a message containing by=
tes to Chain B, and Chain B executes whatever instructions are contained in=
 the bytes.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>For times when that message co=
ntains instructions to transfer tokens, LayerZero Labs introduced the </spa=
n><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/64587889-850a-4bfb-888a-086ae5f9=
518b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" re=
l style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">Omnichain F=
ungible Token</a><span> (OFT) Standard. According to the docs, &#8220;This =
standard works by burning tokens on the source chain whenever an omnichain =
transfer is initiated, sending a message via the protocol and delivering a =
function call to the destination contract to mint the same number of tokens=
 burned, creating a </span><strong>unified supply</strong><span> across bot=
h networks.&#8221;&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font=
-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">With OFT, there is no =
pot of tokens sitting somewhere &#8211; tokens are burned on one side and r=
e-minted on the other.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>LayerZero launched =
on St. Patrick&#8217;s Day, March 17, 2022. Alongside the launch, the Layer=
Zero Founders built a bridge, </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redire=
ct/a9ac2298-79e0-4387-b2db-745de74118d3?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_Z=
lNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-=
decoration: underline;">Stargate</a><span>, to show it off. (It&#8217;s now=
 governed by a DAO.) Stargate uses the LayerZero protocol to move native as=
sets instead of locking and wrapping, and raises an important distinction.&=
#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">LayerZero is the messaging rails that ope=
rate underneath liquidity transfers. Bridges, like Stargate, operate on top=
 of LayerZero. Those bridge smart contracts still have locked liquidity in =
them for non-OFT tokens, and hackers can still target the bridge&#8217;s li=
quidity pools. The more protocols adopt standards like OFT, and the Ethereu=
m community&#8217;s similar xERC20, the less opportunity there is for hacke=
rs.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-heig=
ht: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Since launch day, LayerZero </span><a =
href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/667c1b4e-46c3-4a54-945b-f7916ec28857?=
j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">has delivered</a=
><span> over 87 million messages, with over 31,000 smart contracts live on =
Mainnet, and Bryan tells me that over $40 billion has moved through its pip=
es&#8230; </span><strong>all without a hack</strong><span>.&#160;</span></p=
