ascinating as I did. It&#8217;s business development and technical sales, o=
ut in the open, with debate among participants and observers, meant to conv=
ince a community instead of a single buyer.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"col=
or: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;"><span>As the conversation continued over the next month, the community s=
eemed to agree that launching on Binance was a good idea, but weren&#8217;t=
 convinced that Hyperloop was the solution. So more bridges and messaging p=
rotocols threw their hat in the ring: first deBridge, then Celer, and then,=
 on January 24th, </span><strong>Wormhole</strong><span>.&#160;</span></p><=
p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>After the $326 million hack in 2022, Wormhole upgrad=
ed itself. It shifted its architecture from bridge to cross-chain messaging=
, spent $2.5 million on bug bounties, and underwent a </span><a href=3D"htt=
ps://substack.com/redirect/15ee9899-d83f-424f-97bf-e6658fb36db8?j=3DeyJ1Ijo=
iOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color=
: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">number of audits</a><span>.=
&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The day after Wormhole entered the fray,=
 LayerZero did too.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size:=
 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">With Wormhole and LayerZero =
in the ring, the competition pretty quickly became a choice between these t=
wo heavyweights, each backed by heavier-weights. LayerZero was backed by a1=
6z crypto, also an early Uniswap investor and large UNI tokenholder, and Wo=
rmhole was backed by high-frequency trading firm and crypto market maker Ju=
mp Trading, which incubated the project and which also owns a significant a=
mount of UNI tokens (and therefore votes).&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(=
64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Over =
the next week, there was a lot of back and forth among UNI community member=
s, including university blockchain clubs from Stanford, Penn, Michigan, and=
 Berkeley. The conversation covered a few different topics simultaneously: =
whether there should even be a vote on a single bridge provider, what the p=
rocess for decisions like this would be going forward, and whether Uniswap =
should wait and use a multi-bridge or multi-message aggregation solution.&#=
160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But there was a time constraint. As a16z crypto&#=
8217;s Porter Smith wrote, &#8220;Given the expiration of Uniswap V3&#8217;=
s BUSL license in early April, we&#8217;re generally in favor of deploying =
Uni V3 to other chains before that date to avoid the copy-paste rush that w=
ill likely ensue otherwise.&#8221;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">So a choice needed =
to be made quickly, and for the purposes of our discussion, it came down to=
 verification models:&#160;</p><ul style=3D"margin-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li=
 style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"bo=
x-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height:=
 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>Wormhole:</=
strong><span> secured by 19 Guardians, 13 of whom must attest to a message =
for it to go through. The validator set is comprised of independent validat=
ors, chosen by Wormhole.</span></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; =
mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb=
(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom:=
 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>LayerZero:</strong><span> secured by an Ora=
cle, with Chainlink as the default but configurable by the application, in =
this case, Uniswap.&#160;</span></p></li></ul><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64=
, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The fact th=
at this is how the battle shaped up was an error in communication on LayerZ=
ero Labs&#8217; part, Bryan told me. It became a contest of whose validatio=
n set or verification model was more trusted by the market; he wishes they&=
#8217;d made it more clear that LayerZero doesn&#8217;t compete at that lev=
el, that as a transport and messaging protocol, it&#8217;s verification agn=
ostic. If they&#8217;d messaged it right, he thinks the choice should have =
come down to:&#160;</p><ul style=3D"margin-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li style=
=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizi=
ng: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>Wormhole:</strong=
><span> trust Wormhole&#8217;s validator set and verification model, which =
is locked in&#160;</span></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-sp=
ecial-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 6=
4, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; pa=
dding-left: 4px;"><strong>LayerZero: </strong><span>choose whichever valida=
tor set and verification model Uniswap wants, with the freedom to swap out =
Oracles at any point.</span></p></li></ul><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But they didn&#=
8217;t message it well, and initially, community members like Kydo from Sta=
nford Blockchain leaned in favor of Wormhole, &#8220;because of its diverse=
 validator set.&#8221; Kydo was concerned that LayerZero relied heavily on =
Chainlink&#8217;s oracle relay service.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64,=
 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">LayerZer=
o spoke with Stanford Blockchain and clarified its proposal, recommending t=
hat Uniswap switch out Chainlink for a &#8220;gasless oracle run by a minim=
um of 5+ significant Uniswap delegates.&#8221; Kydo responded:&#160;</p><bl=
ockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #51b4e9; margin: 20px 0; padding: =
0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>Thank you for posting this upd=
ated proposal, LayerZero.</em></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>=
We believe this proposal addresses a lot of the questions we have raised be=
fore. And their ability to change Chainlink with a set of Uniswap-aligned o=
racle validators is very promising.</em></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, =
64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 2=
0px;"><em>For total transparency, LayerZero reached out to us and addressed=
 most of our technical concerns.</em></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64)=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px=
;"><em><span>One thing we believe we undervalued, in our initial assessment=
, is the </span><strong>immutability</strong><span> of the bridge. Many hac=
ks happen because of simple upgrades. </span><strong>Under LayerZero&#8217;=
s design, the underlying infrastructure (LayerZero protocol) is immutable. =
The changeable parts, the Oracle (header sync) and Relayer (MIP), can only =
be changed by Uniswap governance.</strong></em></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(6=
4, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-=
left: 20px;"><em>Given the immutability and LayerZero&#8217;s new proposed =
Oracle, we would like to signal to the community that we have tentatively m=
oved LayerZero as our preferred bridge provider for BNB.</em></p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>We would also love to see more documentati=
on provided from LayerZero&#8217;s side, especially around the oracle and r=
elayer services.</em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>There&#8217;s=
 an important distinction in there, which Kydo alluded to but didn&#8217;t =
call out specifically: </span><strong>LayerZero and Wormhole are fundamenta=
lly different products.</strong><span>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: r=
gb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">La=
yerZero is solely the transport layer, and Wormhole is also the verificatio=
n layer. Because of that, Uniswap could swap out Chainlink for its own veri=
fier set. With Wormhole, if you want the pipes, you also need to use its 13=
-of-19 Guardian model.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">&#8220;We felt like the U=
niswap forum was more of a failure on our part to properly message the prot=
ocol and the role it plays,&#8221; Bryan told me. &#8220;They expected us t=
