if you&#8217;re connecting chains that handle execution and consensus in si=
milar ways, like EVM-compatible chains, they argue, but not if you want to =
connect chains across different compatibility groups, like connecting Solan=
a and Ethereum.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>They propose an </span><st=
rong>omnichain messaging protocol (OMP)</strong><span> that leverages &#822=
0;foundational invariants underlying all blockchains to create a chain-agno=
stic protocol that semantically unites interoperation between onchain contr=
acts, between chains in the same compatibility group, and between different=
 chain groups.&#8221;&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>In other word=
s, like TCP/IP created a &#8220;language of the Internet,&#8221; LayerZero =
Labs is attempting to create a </span><strong>&#8220;language of the Omnich=
ain.&#8221;</strong><span>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 6=
4); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">LayerZero Labs=
 writes that an OMP has two responsibilities:&#160;</p><ol style=3D"margin-=
