olor: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px=
 0;">That&#8217;s what LayerZero enables. Developers can pair the security =
of Ethereum with the speed of an L2, tap into liquidity across chains, and =
build apps that are composable no matter where the best Lego blocks happen =
to live.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>And as for you? If you haven&#821=
7;t played around with crypto for the past year, I think you&#8217;ll be su=
rprised at how much better it&#8217;s getting. Go bridge some ETH to Optimi=
sm or Base on </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/3fe5f2b1-d329=
-4816-84a9-3d4f23758ae4?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbq=
Osa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: unde=
rline;">Stargate</a><span> and bridge it back to Ethereum mainnet. It&#8217=
;s a smoother experience than you might remember from the last cycle.&#160;=
</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>LayerZero still has a long way to go. It=
&#8217;s live in a number of use cases, including DEXes (Trader Joe), stabl=
ecoins (MIM), and games (</span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/d4=
55d8d7-b112-40b5-990f-d5e6e23dc3de?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaM=
ZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decor=
ation: underline;">Parallel</a><span>), but developers have barely scratche=
d the surface of the omnichain app design space. Even with a better product=
, it will have to hook into more chains, win BD battles, and clearly commun=
icate to developers why and how they can build better products on top of it=
s infrastructure.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But wherever we are in =
the price cycle, that&#8217;s the cycle that excites me most: better infras=
tructure enabling better applications that bring more people onchain withou=
t forcing them to sacrifice security or performance. I think LayerZero v2 i=
s a big step in that cycle, and I&#8217;m excited to see what developers bu=
ild on it.&#160;</p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;"><hr =
